    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) powered by the iconic S54 3.2L inline-six. This high-compression powerplant features individual throttle bodies and Double VANOS variable valve timing, delivering a linear power band up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed via a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M-differential lock for precise torque distribution. This example has undergone essential preventative maintenance, including rod bearing service and rear subframe reinforcement. The suspension geometry remains true with refreshed bushings, providing the communicative steering and chassis balance synonymous with the M-division. While presenting minor cosmetic patina, the drivetrain and kinematics are optimized for immediate performance use.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 28
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Used sedan. Good condition. Regular maintenance performed. Clean title. Reliable engine. Interior and exterior well-kept. Ready for immediate sale.",
      "price": 34500.0,
